By the mid-[[:en:Heian period|Heian period]], the positions became hereditary among the {{ill|Sanuki clan|ja|讃岐氏|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sanuki clan|qq=}} and {{ill|Imomune clan|ja|惟宗氏|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Imomune clan|qq=}}, but during the medieval period, these were replaced by the renowned {{ill|Sakanoue clan|ja|坂上氏|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sakanoue clan|qq=}} and {{ill|Nakahara clan|ja|中原氏|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nakahara clan|qq=}}<ref>In [[:en:Kenkyū|Kenkū 2]] (1191), [[:en:Ōe no Hiromoto|Nakahara no Hiromoto]] was appointed as Myōhō Hakase through the recommendation of {{ill|Tsuchimikado no Michichika|ja|土御門通親|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsuchimikado no Michichika|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 源通親}} while serving as the {{ill|Mandokoro Betto|ja|政所別当|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mandokoro Betto|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} of the [[:en:Kamakura shogunate|Kamakura Shogunate]]. This appointment was harshly criticized by [[:en:Fujiwara no Kanezane|Kujō Kanezane]] as violating precedent, as Hiromoto was of the {{ill|Monjōdō|ja|明経道|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Monjōdō|qq=}} branch of the Nakahara family (who later adopted the Ōe surname). However, Hiromoto resigned on November 5 of that year. It is generally believed that this resignation was due to displeasure from [[:en:Minamoto no Yoritomo|Minamoto no Yoritomo]] over free appointments, but another view suggests that Yoritomo had plans to place the {{ill|Office of Police and Justice|lt=Office of Police and Justice|lt=Kebiishi|ja|検非違使庁|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kebiishi|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 検非違使}} under the control of the Shogunate and appointed Hiromoto to oversee the legal aspects but made him resign after the {{ill|Kenkū 2 Uprising|ja|建久二年の強訴|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kenkū 2 Uprising|qq=}} could not be prevented (Tomohiro Saeki, ''Ichijō Yoshiyasu and Early Kamakura Public-Private Relations,'' ''Ancient Culture'' 564, 2006).</ref>.
